8. The device as recited in claim 5, 
wherein means (110) are provided with which a first vehicle acceleration variable (axAntriebMod), particularly the vehicle acceleration theoretically to be expected, is ascertained at least as a function of the torque variable, particularly using a mathematical model; 
and means (105) are provided with which a second vehicle acceleration variable (axAktAntrieb), particularly the vehicle acceleration actually setting in, is ascertained as a function of the wheel speeds of the non-driven wheels; the mass variable being ascertained as a function of the first and the second vehicle acceleration variable.

10. The device as recited in claim 1, 
wherein means (107) are provided with which a second vehicle motion variable (phiaxAntrieb) is ascertained; 
for the ascertainment of the mass variable, the second vehicle motion variable being compared to comparison values predefined for the second vehicle motion variable, and the mass variable being ascertained as a function of these comparisons.
